        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 1:38AM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 137 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Boonville, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boonville, Newburgh, Rockport, Grandview, Eureka, and Chrisney.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
